At least 15 young students reportedly died and several others injured in a major fire that broke out in a building housing a coaching centre in the Surat town of western state Gujarat Friday. According to local media reports, there were around 50 students inside the coaching centre in the "Takshila Commercial Complex" when the fire broke out. TV channels showed young students trying to jump out from the fourth floor of the ill-fated building in a bid to save their lives. Those who jumped out of the building were injured and have been admitted to a local hospital. Latest reports said that the fire has been doused. Further details of the fire incident are awaited. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star